# docs/images/ — plots & figures for the cursus documentation
#
# Put raster plots (PNG/JPG) and SVG figures here. Reference them from a doc
# page with a RELATIVE link, e.g. from docs/architecture/compile-pipeline.md:
#     ![Compile pipeline flow](../images/compile-pipeline.png)
#
# This serves BOTH doc surfaces from one source:
#   - MkDocs (code.amazon.com Releases-tab site) renders the relative link directly.
#   - The wiki: scripts/transform_docs.py (in AmazonCursusWikiDocsCDK) copies these
#     files into lib/assets/wiki/images/ and auto-injects the WaC `attachments:`
#     front matter per page so w.amazon.com uploads them.
#
# WaC limits (per page): <= 20 attachments, <= 1.9 MB each, <= 2.5 MB total.
# Prefer mermaid fenced code blocks for flow/arch/sequence diagrams — they render
# natively on both surfaces with no attachment plumbing and no size limits.
#
# This .gitkeep keeps the folder tracked; it is NOT a *.md file, so neither MkDocs
# nor the transform treats it as a page. Delete it once real images live here.
